import React from 'react' import { Link } from 'react-router-dom'; import { Fragment, useState } from 'react' import { Dialog, Disclosure, Popover, Transition } from '@headlessui/react' import { ArrowPathIcon, Bars3Icon, ChartPieIcon, CursorArrowRaysIcon, FingerPrintIcon, SquaresPlusIcon, XMarkIcon, } from '@heroicons/react/24/outline' import { ChevronDownIcon, PhoneIcon, PlayCircleIcon } from '@heroicons/react/20/solid' const products = [ { name: 'Free Party Hall', description: 'Only food menu charges will consider', href: '#', icon: ChartPieIcon }, { name: 'Family Restorent', description: 'Veg & Non-Veg Manu, Safe Family Lunch/Dinner', href: '#', icon: CursorArrowRaysIcon }, { name: 'Food Delivery Services', description: 'Get food in 35 min at your doorstep', href: '#', icon: FingerPrintIcon }, { name: 'Lodging', description: 'Family Rooms, Corporate Rooms, Couple Friendly Rooms', href: '#', icon: SquaresPlusIcon }, { name: 'Meeting Hall', description: 'Meeting Hall, with table and chairs', href: '#', icon: ArrowPathIcon }, ] const callsToAction = [ { name: 'Check Hotel Interior', href: 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5GqTwfOKkI8', icon: PlayCircleIcon }, { name: 'Contact sales', href: 'tel:+918788233054', icon: PhoneIcon }, ] function classNames(...classes) { return classes.filter(Boolean).join(' ') } const Header = () => { const [mobileMenuOpen, setMobileMenuOpen] = useState(false) return (
